And that's what we call dullness and lethargy.

393
00:46:40,811 --> 00:46:56,876
And over the next couple of days, I hope that the business of sleep imbalance will have been sorted and you'll be very clear to yourself that any sleepiness that comes to the day is in fact dullness and lethargy and is not tiredness.

394
00:46:58,197 --> 00:46:59,880
One can be quite strict about that.

395
00:47:00,012 --> 00:47:05,440
And there, of course, the attitude is simply to stay awake and to be with it, to feel it, you see.

396
00:47:05,760 --> 00:47:06,802
Remember, it is an energy.

397
00:47:08,264 --> 00:47:11,849
It doesn't feel like an energy because it's a sort of collapse into nothingness.

398
00:47:12,210 --> 00:47:13,731
Something's dragging us down.

399
00:47:14,032 --> 00:47:17,317
It's a dullness, dull, heavy feeling.

400
00:47:18,458 --> 00:47:24,007
So the attitude there is basically to stay awake as best one can.

401
00:47:24,086 --> 00:47:26,070
So that's why you open your eyes, you stand up.

402
00:47:27,467 --> 00:47:36,181
And if in a sitting it just becomes ridiculous and you just find yourself nodding and banging your head on the floor, then go for a gentle walk.

403
00:47:38,364 --> 00:47:40,407
And none of this stuff do you fight.

404
00:47:40,706 --> 00:47:42,550
You're not trying to annihilate it.

405
00:47:42,590 --> 00:47:44,231
You're not trying to get rid of it.

406
00:47:44,472 --> 00:47:46,416
You're not trying to overcome it.

407
00:47:46,456 --> 00:47:47,637
You're not trying to beat it.

408
00:47:47,677 --> 00:47:49,018
You're not trying to be better than it.

409
00:47:50,081 --> 00:47:51,722
You're just trying to attend.

410
00:47:53,125 --> 00:47:54,266
See them all as patients.

411
00:47:55,208 --> 00:47:56,309
They're all little illnesses.

412
00:47:56,797 --> 00:47:58,818
And they just need attending to, that's all.

413
00:48:00,902 --> 00:48:02,704
And that's the quality of awareness, you see.

414
00:48:03,083 --> 00:48:03,644
Attention.

415
00:48:05,447 --> 00:48:08,471
And you can flavor the attention with kindness.

416
00:48:11,974 --> 00:48:17,061
You can look upon these things with compassion, you see.

417
00:48:22,246 --> 00:48:24,610
And that often softens the process, by the way.

418
00:48:24,994 --> 00:48:31,751
It undermines a negativity towards them by seeing that these are little illnesses, little dis-eases.

419
00:48:33,456 --> 00:48:36,844
And that's, I think, a very skillful way to look at it.

420
00:48:57,648 --> 00:49:00,070
Are there any questions?

421
00:49:00,170 --> 00:49:02,012
Anything come up?

422
00:49:12,606 --> 00:49:16,650
Sounds as though I've perfectly described the problem of desire.

423
00:49:19,014 --> 00:49:21,978
May my words be of assistance.

424
00:49:21,998 --> 00:49:26,422
May you be liberated sooner rather than later.

425
00:49:29,474 --> 00:49:31,586
Thank you.

